Luxx, lookin like a million bucks ✨🏁✨ branding for @luxxnoirlondon

For this project, Luxx wanted a modern, chromed-out logo that incorporated a star. After a few very abstract options, we landed on this bold typeface which oddly enough reminds me of a racing typefaces, so funny the promo theme was literal drag racing 🤩 Very excited to see what Luxx brings to S15!

Who else from Season 15 do you want to see me work with? Tag them below 👇

Marcia! Marcia! Marcia! ✨🌻✨ branding for a queen so great she has the same name 3 times; @marciax3nyc

The Marcia Marcia Marcia logo draws inspiration from 70’s glam: think Twiggy; simply stated but visually impactful. The modern-vintage typography features a tight line-height (‘leading’ in design talk) and is finished off with an adjusted M nestled into place, making the relationship between the names more intentional! 

Loved working on this project! Thank you @fiercelyyouentertainment for thinking of me 🤩🥰

Pink on pink, everything in-sync 💕 @khloecoulee 

photo by @dragfiles

2022 a major year for me as a graphic artist — this year was not only my 5th year as a full-time freelance artist but I also achieved a personal goal to work more in the music industry. I did this all while managing Shea and maintaining a wide-variety of clients who trust my artistic vision. It is truly so crazy to see myself manifest this goal: a piece of my work hit #1 on the iTunes US Charts for the first time ever and the same song, I’m Good (Blue), was streamed over a billion times 👽🥹 I even got to work on a super secret project for a literal pop ICON which hopefully sees the light of day!

Thank you everyone for your love and support during this year. I feel very lucky and grateful to wake up and do what I do every single day, it’s not always easy or fun being your own self-sustaining business, but it is very fulfilling and rewarding 🖤🖤🖤

Art for @SheaCoulee’s The Lipstick Ball tour 💋🪩 Premiering this spring in The UK and Europe, this tour fleshes out the world of Shea’s 2017 film Lipstick City! Can’t wait to share the trailer and other visuals with you soon — grab tix now at SheaCoulee.com

photo by @dragfiles
using assets by @blkmarket

Branding for Sissy That Talk Show with Joseph Shepherd 🔅 For this logo, Joseph wanted something strong, simple and effective that was reminiscent of late night talk shows. Using one of my favorite typefaces, Knockout, I created a bold yet balanced logo and added a little flair with a minimal neon glow effect. 

Congrats to @josephashepherd on his new @mompodcasts YouTube series, a variety show that features some of todays top drag stars!

Branding for LA singer @freddieseipoldt 🧊 This logo is inspired by late 90’s/early Y2K R&B, West Coast rap, and hyper-pop; but with a contemporary update. I polished this logo off with a blue horizon chrome and star-gaze afterglow to really showcase the real estate of each character!
.
.
Loved working on this logo and can’t wait to share some of the other branding projects I’ve been working on with you all soon 🤩🤓

As a freelancer, not every project reaches the finish line and that’s totally okay! 

Here are some logos and album titles I worked on for @avamax last year for her new album, Diamonds & Dancefloors 💎 For the logo Ava wanted her name mixed into a Diamond motif and for the Album titles, she wanted something sharp and shattered. These were some of the options I presented that I really enjoy and wanted to share.

I’m hoping to do some more of these posts when the situation allows — hope you all enjoy! 🤩

Logo design for @iamanetra ⚡️ For this branding project, Anetra wanted something bold and impactful — reminiscent of Chromatica yet still unique. I used the typeface Vivaldi (a favorite of mine) and modernized it with some sharp points and sexy curves as well as playing with the relationship between the letters. I added a custom thermal chrome stylization to finish this off project — swipe to see the details! Had a great time working on this branding as it was very much my personal style as well.

Branding for @nubiatour 🔥 I joined the creative team for Nubia in 2019 to help create the visual identity and motion graphics for the live numbers… and after 3 amazing premiere shows in NYC, Nubia was sidelined by the pandemic. 

This year when creative team reconvened we agreed the original branding needed a modern update: so, I took elements of the previous logo and updated it to a more angular and less rounded approach, @randallstarr and I then bounced the logo back and forth making small tweaks and visually balancing. 

This is one of my takes on the stylization, a modern-day Black Panther inspired piece featuring cool neon inlays, bold metal type and a flaming background to add some warmth. 

Tix on sale tomorrow so make sure you sign up NOW at NubiaTour.com now!!

Very excited to share the branding I created for RHOBH and singer Erika Jayne @theprettymess ✨💎✨

Erika was inspired by the striking simplicity of fashion branding, so after a few options I went back to basics and created a custom bold EJ monogram and paired it with a chic san serif typeface for balance, finishing it off with a gilded gold stylization. Something timeless that could work for many different uses! 

And who knew it would make its debut helping announce her Las Vegas residency?! 

Big thanks to @mikeyminden for the opportunity 🙌

Still reeling from last nights The Lipstick Ball debut in LA ✨ I helped produce the event, book the talent, created all of the key art and a good portion of the visuals plus ran visuals during the show. A huge undertaking but thank you @sheacoulee for always trusting and believing in me 🖤 and thank you SO much @khloecoulee @kenziecoulee @denalifoxx @itstayce @xosonique @thequeenpriyanka and surprise guest @luxxnoirlondon — this lineup was a literal dream for me to work with and I absolutely cannot wait until we bring this show to other cities!!

and thank you @brendon_brown_ @sarahjose__ @adellynp @maxwellesposito @mydadsdead @justdoinnitt @kidalienmusic and everyone else who helped make the first fully-produced show by Maison Couleé a success!!

Key art for @sheacoulee’s The Lipstick Ball: LA 🪩 for this art I was inspired by vintage rock and disco posters with a modern update! 

Shea photo by @studiomarchal 
Gradient map by @mattyvogel with slight adjustments

Key Art and Branding for @nubiatour Juneteenth Celebration 🔥 for this poster each cast member submitted approved photos of varying styles with part of my job being to somehow make everything cohesive. I took each image and adjusted the wardrobe to an all-black motif, a very labor-intensive task if you’ve every isolated 6 girls from photo backgrounds and then traced only their outfits. I finished poster with Nubia branding featuring custom neon inlays and a flaming border to help it really pop against the purple background! Get your tix now at NubiaTour.com — this show is going to be everything and more!!

Had a very cool life/career moment this week and wanted to share! 

I’m so so so mind-blown to have received an @riaa_awards double platinum record in recognition of the artwork I did for “I’m Good (Blue)” by @beberexha and @davidguetta. It’s a very surreal moment that a quick turnaround design project has resulted in so many firsts for me and I’m forever grateful for this milestone. Being a freelance artist isn’t easy but moments like this are very rewarding!

Thank you so much to @sheacoulee and @mydadsdead for surprising me with this amazing gift I’ll cherish forever! It means so much to me, even more coming from two of my favorite people. 

And thank you @adellynp for the opportunity and always rooting for me!

One In A Million artwork for @beberexha and @davidguetta 💫 this prismatic glass type treatment is my first project using 3D rendering in Blender with finishing touches done in Photoshop! 

Thank youuu again @adellynp for the opportunity 🙌

I’ve been working on a *major* overhaul of my website so there will be LOTs of new work soon but while I was looking through some old files I found this logo draft I created for @thekandymuse! We ended up not using this but two years later I still really enjoy this intertwined design which juxtaposes editorial and street typography 🤩

I’m honored to share my latest collab, a merch collection of 6 designs inspired by the legendary words of @britneyspears! ✨🎤✨ 

Available now at BritneySpears.com in support of her book, “The Woman In Me,” 📚🖋️ I created these designs to celebrate Britney’s journey, resilience, and unapologetic spirit! 

The first design boldly displays Britney’s unforgettable June 2021 statement: “I wasn’t good, I was great” - an iconic moment in her fight for independence.

As someone who grew up listening to Britney, I’m thrilled to be working with one of the greatest artists of our generation on her comeback journey 🙌 

Stay tuned, I can’t wait to share the rest of this release with you!

#britneyspears #thewomaninme

Your support truly means the world to me and collaborating with Pop royalty @britneyspears is a dream turned reality! 🌟 

Now, let’s unveil more of the magic: a bold t-shirt inspired by My Prerogative that exclaims freedom and a Stronger-inspired beanie that serves as a daily reminder of Britney’s ever-growing strength. 

Available now at BritneySpears.com in support of her book, “The Woman In Me,” 📚🖋️ I created these designs to celebrate Britney’s journey, resilience, and unapologetic spirit!

#britneyspears #thewomaninme

Closing out the @britneyspears Legendary Quotes collection are my final two designs:

The first is a Work Bitch inspired design featuring Britney herself and the second is a simple yet powerful declaration, as Britney fearlessly reclaims her name.

Available now at BritneySpears.com in support of her book, “The Woman In Me,” 📚🖋️ I created these designs to celebrate Britney’s journey, resilience, and unapologetic spirit!

Logo for @estitties 💖 A bold custom Old English typography inspired by West Coast cholo culture, this logo exudes strong and powerful energy, yet surprises with feminine curves and a custom pink airbrush finish!

Capsule collection for the 25th Anniversary of the Britney Spears debut album “…Baby One More Time” ✨ concepted and designed by me! 

I have such vivid memories of being a kid listening to the blue and beige disc in my CD player so I’m very honored to have been able to create these designs — especially since it’s the best selling debut album by a female artist of all time!! 

Available now at BritneySpears.com
